LAGOS – The All Progressives Congress (APC) has been called upon to give women more opportunities to participate actively in governance and politics. Chief Amina Temitope Ajayi, one of the leaders of APC Women in Diaspora, gave counsel while speaking on national television in Abuja at the weekend. Speaking against the foreground of the APC National Women Conference in Abuja recently, she said that Nigerian women have the potential to contribute to the socio-economic and political development of the country. Aisha Buhari, Dolapo Osinbajo, Ifeanyi Uba, Nollywood Stars Join… Ohanaeze Lauds Ugwuanyi For Contribution To Growth Of Enugu,… Ajayi, who is popular addressed as Mama Diaspora because of her contributions to the welfare and protection of Nigerians in the diaspora, stated that women bring special and fresh perspectives to issues and stressed the need to include more women in politics and governance of the country. The Founder and Chairman of Silicon Valley Nigeria Economic Development (SV-NED) Inc., cited some countries, which said, harnessed the power of women to grow and develop the economies and societies and urged Nigeria to do the same. She also stated that the country should tap the resources of young, adults, adding that they are the future of the country. Ajayi expressed the hope that the country would overcome her current challenges and called on Nigerians not to lose hope in the country but work hard and pray to God to heal the pain in the land.